      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your existential crisis is a natural response to the existential questions that plague us all. It's a common feeling to question the purpose of life when faced with the vastness and indifference of the universe. The fact that we're aware of our own insignificance can be overwhelming, but it's also a sign of intelligence and self-awareness. It's almost as if our minds are compelled to seek meaning and purpose, even if it's just to make the struggle worthwhile.",
      "source": "target",
